<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Transition Training and Technical Assistance Specialist</a></h2>
<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Transition Training and Technical Assistance Specialist<br />
<strong>SUPERVISOR</strong>: Sean Roy<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: FT, Exempt
</p>

<p>
The person in this position is responsible for developing and delivering training and technical assistance for PACER projects with a primary focus on transition related issues including self determination, career development, postsecondary education, the vocational rehabilitation service system, supported employment, and independent living. 
</p>

<h3>RESPONSIBILITIES:</h3>
<ol>
<li>Provide individual phone assistance, advocacy, and information on transition planning, vocational rehabilitation services, employment, access to postsecondary education, and other disability issues </li>
<li>Prepare and conduct workshops for parents on the Rehabilitation Act, transition and related disability topics </li>
<li>Prepare and conduct workshops for youth with disabilities on self determination, workplace accommodations and other timely transition and disability related topics </li>
<li>Prepare and conduct in-service training for professionals who work with youth with disabilities on disability and transition related topics </li>
<li>Coordinate national conferences and monthly teleconferences on timely transition topics designed to address the technical assistance needs of staff of other federally funded parent information and training centers </li>
<li>Develop individualized technical assistance agreements with parent information and training projects funded by the Rehabilitation Services Administration in collaboration with other technical assistance staff </li>
<li>Coordinate scheduling of internal cross-project information sharing sessions among PACER staff working on transition related issues </li>
<li>Contribute to the creation and review of new and existing PACER publications on transition and disability related issues</li>
<li>Represent PACER on committees and task forces relating to independent living, self-advocacy, employment, transition and rehabilitation issues</li>
<li>Manage a national listserv devoted to transition-focused issues, information and resources.</li>
<li>Facilitate cross-agency collaboration to improve transition outcomes through Communities of Practice, resource mapping, or other project specific activities</li>
<li>Other project related activities as assigned.</li>
</ol>

<h3>REQUIREMENTS</h3>
<ul>
<li>College degree</li>
<li>Experience with disability issues affecting youth with disabilities and their families.</li>
<li>Experience working with culturally diverse families and communities.</li>
<li>Experience in conference planning.</li>
<li>Public speaking skills.</li>
<li>Ability to multi-task and prioritize project assignments effectively.</li>
<li>Must be self motivated and able to work independently.</li>
<li>Ability to meet timelines, manage a project, and give attention to details.</li>
<li>Ability to travel</li>
<li>Basic computer and internet skills. </li>
</ul>

<p>
<strong>SALARY</strong>: To be determined based on experience.<br />
Position available immediately. Parents of children with disabilities are encouraged to apply.
</p>

